Dialog:
Doubt thou the stars are fire;
POLONIUS	Doubt that the sun doth move;
POLONIUS	Doubt truth to be a liar;
POLONIUS	But never doubt I love.
POLONIUS	O dear Ophelia! I am ill at these numbers: I have not art to reckon my groans; but that I love thee best, O most best! believe it. Adieu.
POLONIUS	Thine evermore, most dear lady, whilst this machine is to him,HAMLET.
